when.description:
Filters are used to further narrow down the conditions that must be met for
an action to be taken. Filters are optional.
When conditionals in these repeated entries are ANDed for this rule.
Sample:
     when: [
       {
         match_provider_type: {
           value_match_criteria: EQUALS,
           string_value: "AWS"
         },
       },
       {
         match_provider_tag: {
           value_match_criteria: EQUALS,
           string_value: "prod"
         }
       }
     ]
When empty, the rule is applied to all requests.

configAccessRequestAnalysisRule.title:
AccessRequestAnalysisRule is a set of rules and conditions that must be met for
an action to be taken by Andromeda intelligence while reviewing an access request.
The rules is analysed in the engine like so:
   aggregates = []
   if when(provider.type == AWS && provider.type == Azure) && condition(policy.risk < 50) {
	    aggregates.append(auto_approve)
   }
   if when(provider.environment == prod) && condition(policy.risk < 20) {
	    aggregates.append(auto_approve)
   }
   if when(provider.type == GCP) && condition(request.duration < "30min") {
	    aggregates.append(auto_approve)
   }
   if when(provider.type == AWS) && condition(identity.termination_date within 30 days) {
	    aggregates.append(ask_for_review)
   }
   analysis.ai_review = compute(aggregates)

